        "type": "two-columns-text",
        "name": null,
        "title": "Best Alternatives to Episerver:",
        "style": null,
        "contentBefore": "<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">There are myriad alternatives for B2B ecommerce platforms. We will look at the positives and negatives of the top Episerver competitors that you should consider:</h3>\n",
        "items": [
            {
                "text": "<p><strong>Virto Commerce</strong></p>\n\n<p>Virto Commerce is the most agile and extensible ecommerce platform available. Specifically designed for enterprise B2B ecommerce, its enterprise clients around the world include: Volvo, Bosch, Heineken, Vivint Smart Home and Rainbow Sandals.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "text": "<p><strong>Pros</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>If you&#39;re in the B2B space, this ecommerce solution is specifically designed for your business. Virto Commerce&#39;s .NET open source platform offers no limits to customization, and future proofs your business as the platform grows and changes as your business needs change.</li>\n\t<li>The architecture is easy to work with and&nbsp;configure and&nbsp;is easily scalable. As an Azure .Net open source platform, you have full control over the code and development of your site.</li>\n\t<li>Virto Commerce has tools to help new store owners, including documentation, samples, forums, tech-support and an enterprise edition to help B2B sellers.</li>\n\t<li>Their leadership team has decades of B2B and enterprise ecommerce experience that they can leverage to help your store succeed.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Cons</strong></p>\n\n<p>As it is not as well known as some of the larger players in the industry like Shopify and Magento, the Virto ecosystem can seem rather small by comparison. Although you can get a store up and running quickly if you know how, without any technical knowledge, it is not going to be plug-and-play like some off the shelf solutions would be. You would need some technical background or a dedicated team to set it up and run Virto Commerce. However, Virto does have a comprehensive training and support system for customers and a team of global partners that can guide your implementation process. <strong>​​​​​​​</strong></p>\n"
            }
        ],
