                "title": "SAP Hybris (Now known as SAP Commerce Cloud)",
                "text": "<p><strong>SAP Hybris</strong></p>\n\n<p>Recently rebranded from SAP Hybris, SAP Commerce Cloud is a well-known cloud ecommerce platform that has been around since the 1990s. It is popular despite it&#39;s monolithic architecture that makes it hard to modify.&nbsp;</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "title": "Pros",
                "text": "<p><strong>Pros</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Ideal for non-tech savvy sellers, it comes equipped with templates for common ecommerce functions. It is easy to customize and integrates well with other services like SAP Cloud platforms that make for a seamless ecommerce process from front to back. SAP Cloud Commerce is also scalable, so it can handle spikes in website traffic during busy shopping days.&nbsp;<br />\n\t&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Cons</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>SAP Commerce Cloud relies on older, monolithic&nbsp;architecture that doesn&#39;t make it easy to integrate micro services which you wish to use.&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li>Being a closed platform, SAP Cloud Commerce does not allow for people to manipulate the source code directly. So, although it is customizable by using the different templates it comes with, if you cannot find a template that fits your exact needs, you cannot dig into the code to fiddle with it yourself.</li>\n\t<li>It also does not have good support and guidance like other platforms on the market.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n"
            }
